<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="1432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Peru/1110:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-06T19:00:00-04:00">April 6,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>361. Your 461, April 4. The Department does not believe it would be
                            desirable to use the new rotenone proposal to bargain for debt
                            settlements.</p>
                        <p>Further, since the proposed prices for rotenone are thought to be
                            necessary to obtain badly needed supplies, the new offer contained in
                            the Department’s 305, March 24 and 341, April l,<note n="55" xml:id="d1432fn55">Neither printed.</note> should be made rather
                            promptly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>